2) Air quality. Air quality monitoring is realized by the State Hydrometeorological Service through a network of 19 stationary posts located in 5 industrial centres of the Republic of Moldova (Chisinau - 6, Balti - 2, Bender - 4, Tiraspol - 3, Ribnita - 2), automatic post at Mateuti and a station in Leova. Observations are carried out in accordance with the European Monitoring and Evaluation Programme and with provisions of the Convention on Long-range Transboundary Air Pollution. The urban air quality is monitored by the Ministry of Health with respect to 8 atmospheric pollutants. The data collected are stored in a special database that is not available for public use. There is only one economic agent in the whole country to have a self-monitoring air quality system, the "Lafarge" Cement Plant.
